It is good to keep components in different files.

REQUIRES node.js and npm

build step to create prod ready 'bundles'


webpack is main tool
    gulp, browserify

cd to app (app.jsx)
    index.html part

npm init -y


    package.json file
    fills in default

npm instal --save react react-dom

npm install --save -dev webpack

npm install --save -dev babel-core babel-loader

npm install --save -dev babel-preset-react babel-preset-es2015


################# config babel

touch .babelrc
    {
        "presets":["react","es2015"]
    }

#### now we can remove the vendor folder.




--only=dev
